  "cases": [
    {
      "case_id": "constellation",
      "title": "The constellation seams",
      "status": "active",
      "headline": "What Agent Governor asks of its siblings \u2014 and how little of it is wired.",
      "dek": "Agent Governor names adapters for standing, the linear accountant, wicket, and night shift. Every one of those files exists. None of the cross-repo integrations is witnessed in running code on main \u2014 they self-describe as SPEC-honoring harness stubs.\n",
      "why": "Turn off every layer but `wired` and this graph nearly empties. That emptiness is the finding, exactly as the intake atlas's empty external_consumer region is. The seams are named (honest), the integrations are not built (also honest). `spec_is_not_wired` keeps the existence of a stub file from masquerading as a working seam.\n"
    },
    {
      "case_id": "internals-standing-spendability",
      "title": "Standing \u2192 Spendability: the spend wall",
      "status": "active",
      "headline": "How a governed spend gets admitted \u2014 or refused before it can spend.",
      "dek": "The orchestrator chains admission \u2192 standing \u2192 spend. Three gates stand between an agent's proposal and any operational effect. Each is wired to running code and a test, names the typed refusal it emits, and carries a recorded adequacy admission.\n",
      "why": "The hero specimen: every edge is `wired`, so it survives the default filter. The admission says a human checked, at a pinned sha, that the cited code establishes the edge \u2014 claimdocs proves the code still resolves and is unchanged, never that it suffices.\n"
    }
  ]
}